# Reuse Inbuilt Tasks

## Rule

**Never create new Tekton Task definitions in this repository.** All pipeline steps must reference tasks already installed by the OpenShift Pipelines operator in the `openshift-pipelines` namespace.

## How to reference tasks

Use the cluster resolver (required for OpenShift Pipelines 1.17+):

```yaml
taskRef:
  resolver: cluster
  params:
    - name: kind
      value: task
    - name: name
      value: git-clone        # task name from openshift-pipelines
    - name: namespace
      value: openshift-pipelines
```

Do **not** use deprecated `kind: ClusterTask`.

## Available inbuilt tasks (use these)

| Task | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `git-clone` | Clone source from Git |
| `buildah` | Build and push container images |
| `maven` | Maven build/test (Java, Camel, Quarkus) |
| `npm` | Node.js scripts and tests |
| `golang-test` | Go tests |
| `python` | Python scripts and tests |
| `openshift-client` | `oc`/`helm` commands, YAML/Kustomize deploy, custom scripts |
| `s2i-java`, `s2i-nodejs`, `s2i-python`, etc. | Source-to-image builds |
| `skopeo-copy` | Copy images between registries |
| `cleanup` | Workspace cleanup |

List tasks on your cluster: `oc get tasks -n openshift-pipelines`

## When you need functionality not covered by a single task

Compose multiple inbuilt tasks in a Pipeline, or use `openshift-client` with a `SCRIPT` parameter for `oc apply`, `oc apply -k`, or `helm upgrade --install`.

## Do not

- Create `kind: Task` YAML files in this repo
- Copy task definitions from Tekton Hub into this repo
- Use Hub/Git resolvers to pull tasks when an inbuilt equivalent exists

## Helm deploy note

Community Helm cluster tasks (`helm-upgrade-from-source`) were removed from the operator in OCP Pipelines 1.17. Use the inbuilt `openshift-client` task with `helm upgrade --install` in the `SCRIPT` parameter instead.
